artition metadata and contents to an image file, for\nflashing."]}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.ReadFromImageFile", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.ReadFromImageBlob", "type": null, "documentation": ["Read/Write logical partition metadata to an image file, for producing a\nsuper_empty.img (for fastboot wipe-super/update-super) or for diagnostics."]}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.WriteSplitImageFiles", "type": null, "documentation": ["Similar to WriteToSparseFile, this will generate an image that can be\nflashed to a device directly. However unlike WriteToSparseFile, it\nis intended for retrofit devices, and will generate one sparse file per\nblock device (each named super_<name>.img) and placed in the specified\noutput folder."]}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetPartitionName", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetPartitionGroupName", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetBlockDevicePartitionName", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetMetadataSuperBlockDevice", "type": null, "documentation": ["Return the block device that houses the super partition metadata; returns\nnull on failure."]}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetTotalSuperPartitionSize", "type": null, "documentation": ["Return the total size of all partitions comprising the super partition."]}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetBlockDevicePartitionNames", "type": null, "documentation": ["Get the list of block device names required by the given metadata."]}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.SlotNumberForSlotSuffix", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.SlotSuffixForSlotNumber", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetPartitionSlotSuffix", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.FindPartition", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liblp.include.liblp.GetPartitionSize", "type": null, "document